<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4544&amp;p=6750#p6750"><![CDATA[
The z-index property is for stacking, X / Y / Z axis. x is left/right, y is up/down and z is close/far.<br /><br />So in example if you have two images or divisible elements that overlap each other by 50% setting the z-index to the left item to 0 and the right item to 1 will make the right item appear on top of the left item.<br /><br />Keep in mind that z-index is a <span style="font-style: italic">position</span> related property and does not correlate with margins. You'll need to use <span style="font-style: italic">position: absolute/relative; left/right: 50px; top/bottom: -100px;</span> like syntax (slashes denote two different options for values, you can only use one value at a time though).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=47">JAB Creations</a> — Thu Mar 03, 2011 2:06 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
